not attaching to the words.

528
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:02,000
Our tendency in academic study is to want to hold on to the words.

529
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,000
We need to read it,

530
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:10,000
hear it,

531
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,000
throw it away,

532
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,000
and keep going.

533
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Even in practice,

534
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,000
we need to realize it,

535
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,000
throw it away,

536
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,000
and keep going.

537
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,000
Whatever it is.

538
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:22,000
And ultimately,

539
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,000
we come to the peak of the mountain.

540
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:25,000
Enlightenment.

541
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,000
Realize it,

542
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,000
throw it away,

543
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,000
and keep going.

544
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:31,000
If you hold on to anything,

545
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:35,000
you've created that dualism again.

546
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,000
So that's why we emphasize,

547
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:41,000
not only material things,

548
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:42,000
even spiritual things.

549
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,000
If you hold on to it,

550
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:46,000
you create an illusion of separateness,

551
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,000
and it's diluted.

